Cicero says, what he has said before on several occasions, that the Romans con- ferred all the honours on him for his merit. Piso got them, because lie was of a noble family. There are several passagesin which Cicero compares the easy road to the high offices of the state for the nobiles, with the difficulties which stood in the way of a man like himself. There is one passage in the Verrine Oratione (ii. 5, c. 70).
